      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That sounds incredibly high. To be honest, I've seen a lot of NGOs claim high efficiency only for it to be a total PR move to hide massive marketing budgets. Can you walk me through how you calculate that 97%? I'd love to see the actual breakdown between what goes to field supplies, logistics, and local staff versus the actual \"admin\" side.",
